data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

**EF Core 11 fully removes sync I/O for the Cosmos DB provider.** In .NET 10 you could opt in to sync-over-async; in .NET 11 that opt-in is gone. Every synchronous call ŌĆö `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()` ŌĆö **will always throw at runtime**, regardless of configuration.

### Fix: convert to async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

Callers of these methods will need to be updated to `await` the results, propagating `async` up the call chain. There is **no workaround** to keep synchronous calls ŌĆö the Cosmos SDK is async-only, and EF Core 11 no longer wraps it.
